1. First install the toolchain
	- For arm-v7 run following command through terminal
	sudo apt-get install gcc-arm-linux-androideabi

2. Download latest version of ffmpeg from ffmpeg.org or use the attached version.

3. Untar ffmpeg tar file in a directory

4. Then cd ffmpeg

5. Configure ffmpeg to use appropriate toolchain

	-For arm-v7
		./configure --enable-cross-compile --arch=arm --target-os=android --cross-prefix=arm-linux-androideabi- --extra-ldflags='-fuse-ld=bfd -fPIE ' --enable-static --disable-shared --extra-cflags='-fPIE' --enable-gpl --enable-pic 	

	- Then do make clean; make
	- This will generate ffmpeg, ffprobe and ffserver binary which can run on any android phone which as arm architecture.

6. For a smaller binary use the following configuration command,
	-For arm-v7
		./configure --enable-cross-compile --arch=arm --target-os=android --cross-prefix=arm-linux-androideabi- --extra-ldflags='-fuse-ld=bfd -fPIE ' --enable-static --disable-shared --extra-cflags='-fPIE' --enable-gpl --enable-pic --enable-runtime-cpudetect

7. Compiling with libx264 and libmp3lame support, we will need --enable-gpl option to compile with libx264 support, make sure that you compiled libx264 and libmp3lame properly for android

	-For arm-v7 
		./configure --enable-cross-compile --arch=arm --target-os=android --cross-prefix=arm-linux-androideabi- --extra-ldflags='-fuse-ld=bfd -L<Path to libmp3lame libs> -L<Path to libx264 libs> -fPIE ' --enable-static --disable-shared --enable-libx264 --enable-libmp3lame --extra-cflags='-I<Path to libx264 include dir> -I<Path to libmp3lame includer dir> -fPIE ' --enable-gpl --enable-runtime-cpudetect --enable-pic	
